KineticLawGenerator

public KineticLawGenerator(CellDesignerPlugin plugin,
                           boolean forceAllReactionsAsEnzymeReaction,
                           boolean generateKineticForAllReaction,
                           short uniUniType,
                           short biUniType,
                           short biBiType,
                           java.util.List<java.lang.String> listOfPossibleEnzymes)
                    throws IllegalFormatException,
                           ModificationException,
                           RateLawNotApplicableException
Parameters:
plugin - An instance of the CellDesigner's plugin interface. *
generateKineticForAllReaction - Indicates weather or not kinetic laws should be generated for each reaction even though a there is already an existing rate law (true).
reversibility - This flag is needed to specify the reversibility information of the given SBML model should be ignored (true) and each reaction is to be treated as a reversible reaction.
forceAllReactionsAsEnzymeReaction - Indicates if even reactions without an explicit catalyst should be modeled as an enzyme catalysed reaction.
uniUniType - Possible values are:
  • 1 = generalized mass-action kinetics
  • 2 = Convenience kinetics
  • 3 = Michaelis-Menten kinetics
biUniType - Possible values are:
  • 1 = generalized mass-action kinetics
  • 2 = Convenience kinetics
  • 4 = Random Order Michealis Menten kinetics
  • 6 = Ordered
biBiType - Possible values are:
  • 1 = generalized mass-action kinetics
  • 2 = Convenience kinetics
  • 4 = Random Order Michealis Menten kinetics
  • 5 = Ping-Pong
  • 6 = Ordered
listOfPossibleEnzymes - A list which contains the names of all species that are accepted to act as enzymes during a reaction. Valid are the following entries (upper and lower case is ignored):
  • ANTISENSE_RNA
  • SIMPLE_MOLECULE
  • RECEPTOR
  • UNKNOWN
  • COMPLEX
  • TRUNCATED
  • GENERIC
  • RNA
Not allowed entries like
  • Phenotype
  • Gene
  • IonChannel
  • Ion
    • will be filtered out of the list.
    Throws:
    IllegalFormatException
    ModificationException
    RateLawNotApplicableException

    createKineticLaw

    public BasicKineticLaw createKineticLaw(PluginModel model,
                                        PluginReaction reaction,
                                        short kinetic,
                                        boolean reversibility)
                                 throws ModificationException,
                                        RateLawNotApplicableException
    Creates a kinetic law for the given reaction, which can be assigned to the given reaction.

    Parameters:
    model - The SBML model, which contains the reaction for which a kinetic law is to be created.
    reaction - The reaction for which a kinetic law is to be created.
    kinetic - valid values:
    1. generalized mass-action
    2. simple convenience/independent convenience
    3. Michaelis-Menten
    4. Random order Michaelis-Menten
    5. Ping-Pong
    6. Ordered
    7. Hill equation
    8. irreversible non-modulated non-interacting enzyme kinetics
    9. Zeroth order forward mass action kinetics
    10. Zeroth order reverse mass action kinetics
    11. Competitive non-exclusive, non-cooperative inihibition
        12. reversibility - If true, a reversible kinetic will be assigned to this reaction and the reversible attribute of the reaction will be set to true.
        Returns:
        A kinetic law for the given reaction.
        Throws:
        RateLawNotApplicableException
        ModificationException

    Returns true if the given astnode or one of its descendents contains some identifier with the given id. This method can be used to scan a formula and for a specific parameter or species and detect weather this component is used by this formula. This search is done using a DFS.

    storeLaw

    public PluginReaction storeLaw(CellDesignerPlugin plugin,
                               PluginKineticLaw kineticLaw,
                               boolean reversibility)
    This method stores a kinetic law for the given reaction in the currently selected model given by the plugin. The kinetic law is passed as a String to this method. A boolean variable tells this method weather the formula is for a reversible or for an irreversible reaction. Afterwards all parameters within this kinetic law are also stored in the given model. There is no need to call the storeParameters method.

    Parameters:
    plugin - The plugin, which contains the model.
    reactionNum - The number of the reaction with the currently selected model in the plugin.
    kineticLaw - A string with the formula to be assigned to the given reaction.
